---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "power basics — ecute.club";
---
<BaseLayout {title}>
  <article class="container">
    <h1>power basics</h1>
    <p>batteries and regulators that keep projects happy. mind <em>voltage</em>, <em>polarity</em>, and <em>current</em>.</p>

    <div class="callout">usb 5 V is common. add a fuse/current limit and polarity protection where it matters.</div>

    <h2>regulators</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>LDO</strong> – simple, a bit of heat; needs headroom (dropout).</li>
      <li><strong>buck (switching)</strong> – efficient step-down; watch noise &amp; layout.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>polarity protection</h2>
    <p>series schottky or ideal-diode mosfet. add a reverse-protection graphic you like later.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
